Dorothea Margaretha "Teddy" Scholten (née van Zwieteren; 11 May 1926 – 8 April 2010) was a Dutch singer and television presenter.
She is known for winning the Eurovision Song Contest 1959 with the song "Een beetje", representing the Netherlands.
In 1950, Scholten was invited by The Coca-Cola Company to perform at a show in the United States.
In 1959, she won the Nationaal Songfestival 1959 with the song "Een beetje", written by Willy van Hemert and Dick Schallies.
In 1959, she won the Nationaal Songfestival 1959 with the song "Een beetje", written by Willy van Hemert and Dick Schallies.
This gave her the right to represent the Netherlands in the Eurovision Song Contest 1959, held in Cannes, France.
Throughout the 1950s and 1960s she appeared in popular television shows in the Netherlands.
In 1965 and 1966, she presented the Nationaal Songfestival, the Dutch national final for the Eurovision Song Contest.
Scholten died in The Hague on 8 April 2010, aged 83.
